The paper deals with the problem of matrix completion, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes algorithms that are tolerant to noise and have small sample complexity. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
